HEADWORD: Profligacy
<hw>Prof"li*ga*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Profligate</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>The quality of state of
being profligate; a profligate or very vicious course of life; a state
of being abandoned in moral principle and in vice;
dissoluteness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

